sentences: Sebastián Obando Giraldo (born 15 October 1994), known professionally as Sebastián Yatra, is a Colombian singer and songwriter.
He rose to prominence in Latin America in 2016 when he released the hit "Traicionera".
"Traicionera" served as the lead single for his 2018 debut album, Mantra, which also featured the single "Sutra", featuring Puerto Rican rapper Dalmata.
After graduating from the Sagemont School in Weston, Florida in 2012, Yatra attended Babson College to study business administration.
In September 2013, Yatra had his first minor hit single, "El psicólogo", which charted in his home country Colombia, as well as Venezuela, Ecuador, Mexico and the United States.

2015 saw launching of two successful singles, "No me llames" featuring Alkilados and "Cómo Mirarte", a repeat hit first as solo and again in a collaboration featuring Kenai and remixed by producers like Kevin ADG, Chan El Genio and Dandee.
The single's accompanying music video, directed by Venezuelan filmmaker Daniel Duran and released on July 28, 2017, features four love stories that all center around partners serenading each other.
Yatra released the album Mantra on May 18, 2018.
In 2018, Yatra voiced the character Migo in the Spanish language version of the computer-animated film Smallfoot.
He released the single "Sutra" featuring Puerto Rican reggaeton artist Dalmata in March 2018, which also peaked at number 26 on the Billboard Hot Latin Songs.
In December 2018, Yatra's single "Ya No Tiene Novio" featuring Mau y Ricky reached number one on the Billboard Latin Airplay chart.
In January 2019, Sebastián Yatra and Reik launched a collaborative work titled “Un Año” (one year).
The single was released alongside his new album Fantasia which was released in April 2019.
In June 2019, Yatra released the track "Runaway" with Daddy Yankee and Natti Natasha, featuring the Jonas Brothers.
His single "Oye", featuring Argentine singer Tini, reached number one on the Billboard Argentina Hot 100 for the week of October 26, 2019.

In October 2019 he was involved in political controversies after expressing his support for the politicians and candidates of the Colombian far-right, including controversial former president Álvaro Uribe.
Yatra collaborated with Mexican rock group Maná in November 2019 to release a new version of the group's 1995 single “No Ha Parado De Llover”.
Yatra collaborated with Mexican rock group Maná in November 2019 to release a new version of the group's 1995 single “No Ha Parado De Llover”.
Maná initiated the collaboration after seeing Yatra cover the song at the 2018 Grammys gala.
In March 2020, he began reading children's books on Instagram Live every night at 8pm EST.
Also in March 2020, he released a remix of his Fantasia song "Falta Amor" featuring Ricky Martin.
In 2021, Yatra recorded the Spanish song "Dos Oruguitas" and its English language version, "Two Oruguitas" for the soundtrack of the Disney animated film Encanto.
"Dos Oruguitas" was one of five songs nominated for Best Original Song for the 2022 Oscars.
His June 2019 song "Runaway" was his first foray into bilingual songwriting.
In December 2019, he collaborated with South Korean boy group Monsta X for the song "Magnetic", which features verses from Yatra in Spanish and a bridge from Monsta X in Spanglish.
